        <section class="mb-16">
          <h2 class="font-montserrat font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[#1e3a5f] mb-6">Why Ute Finance Is Different</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Utes occupy a unique position in Australian vehicle finance because they straddle the line between personal and business use. A tradie's HiLux is a work tool Monday to Friday and a family car on weekends. A farmer's Ranger hauls feed during the week and takes the kids to sport on Saturday. This dual-use nature means the finance structure you choose matters enormously — it can be the difference between claiming thousands in tax deductions or claiming nothing.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">The Ford Ranger was Australia's best-selling vehicle in January 2026, followed by the Toyota HiLux. Together with models like the Isuzu D-MAX, Mitsubishi Triton, Mazda BT-50, and GWM Ute, dual cabs dominate Australian roads. With prices for popular new utes ranging from $35,000 to $75,000+ depending on the variant, choosing the right finance is a significant financial decision.</p>
