        <section class="mb-16">
          <h2 class="font-montserrat font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[#1e3a5f] mb-6">Ute Finance Options</h2>

          <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Consumer Car Loan (Personal Use)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">If the ute is primarily for personal use (less than 50% business), a standard consumer car loan is the appropriate product. This is a straightforward secured loan where the ute acts as security. You cannot claim tax deductions on interest or depreciation, but rates are competitive — from approximately 5.09% p.a. for new vehicles with excellent credit. No ABN required.</p>

          <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Chattel Mortgage (Business Use)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">If the ute is primarily for business (more than 50% business use), a chattel mortgage is almost always the better option. You own the ute from day one, claim the full GST on the purchase price in your next BAS, deduct interest on every repayment, and claim depreciation. For a $65,000 Ford Ranger Wildtrak (GST-inclusive), the GST recovery alone is approximately $5,909. Add interest deductions and depreciation, and the after-tax cost of the ute drops significantly.</p>

          <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Novated Lease (Salary Packaging)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">If you are an employee and your employer offers salary packaging, a novated lease lets you pay for the ute and its running costs from your pre-tax salary. This reduces your taxable income and can save you money on GST, income tax, and running costs. It is available for both new and used vehicles. Note that for utes used primarily for private purposes, FBT may apply — though the operating cost method can minimise FBT if business use is significant.</p>

          <div class="bg-[#0d4d3e]/5 border-l-4 border-[#10b981] rounded-r-lg p-6 my-6">
            <p class="text-[#0d4d3e] font-lato font-light leading-relaxed"><strong>Not sure which structure?</strong> Nik Finance helps you compare the total after-tax cost of each option for your specific situation. We work with your accountant to ensure you choose the structure that delivers the best outcome.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

